permissions.description: Permissions for staff working in access-related function (e.g., Stacks hourlies)
For bibliographers, selectors, subject specialists, etc. to view status of materials, including ordering, funds, cataloging, and circulation
MyAccount permissions for the mylibrary application.
Permission set for apps that need read-only access to inventory records
Permissions for staff working in access-related functions (circulation, courses, stacks, etc.)
Permissions for management-level staff who can perform more work than general staff, but less than Admin-level staff. These can include Operations Managers, Student Supervisors, etc.
Permissions for staff working in access-related functions (circulation staff, ILL staff)
Permissions for staff working in access-related function (e.g., students)

For staff with authorization to create, delete and modify user records, as well as assist certain users with passwords for My Account. Should not be nested under other psets. Should be granted to staff on an as-needed basis.
Administrator-level permissions for a librarian, head of department, assistant head of department. Staff who are able to make policy setting and implements access to staff based on those decisions.
